Dearest ICANN Committe, I can. And I will be the man that gets your vote, because of 3 simple improvements I desire to make in the internet that you have overlooked or deemed unimportant. 1. a more universal incorporation of the internet into everyday life. Here in the USA it is.. but not so in other countries. In order for this to happen, we need to take the internet to other places, regions, even countries 2. Expand domains and recognized characters. There's more to the world than english, and this is actually a sub-part of point number one's plan. Just like XP supports other languages, the internet needs to as well. 3. There are few things more annoying to the experienced computer user than... spyware. As part of my mission w/ my newfound glorious position, all spyware will be removed in the next year from the internet, period. Spyware will be illegal, and punishable by.. fines and stuff
